<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 06 at 11:43PM CDT  by NWS Mobile</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Butler,
southern Crenshaw, northeastern Escambia, southeastern Conecuh and
northern Covington Counties through 1245 AM CDT...
At 1142 PM CDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm 9 miles south of McKenzie, or 11 miles east of
Evergreen, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Andalusia, Opp, Brantley, McKenzie, River Falls, Red Level, Dozier,
Heath, Gantt and Glenwood.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
